search::convertSearchArrayToBoolForm()

Description
    private string search::convertSearchArrayToBoolForm([array $searchArray = NULL])

Parameters
    searchArray
    Builds a string, $results, based on boolean operands contained in the array, $searchArray.

Return Values
    Returns an implode()'ed string, $results, delimited by ' '. 

Examples

    Example #1
	<?php
	    ...
	    public function submit() {
	    ...
	    $this->searchString = $this->convertSearchArrayToBoolForm();
	    ...
	    print_r($this->searchArray);
	    ...
	?>

    Example #2
	<?php
	    ...
	    $tmp = array();
	    ...
	    if($keyword2 == ')' && $parens <= 0) {
		$results[] = '(' . $this->convertSearchArrayToBoolForm($tmp). ')';
		break;
	    }
	    ...
	?>

See Also
    search::submit()
